RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GINGER SPARKLE trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, swung wide entering the stretch and gained ground late while drifting out to get up for the win near the wire. NICOLINO dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path coming around the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught late. ANGELIC STORM bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and chased the winner home. MY SONG AND MELODY veered out and bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, recovered to duel up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the bend and faded in the stretch. SONG OF THE HEART raced in the middle of the pack through the early going, continued around the turn in the two path and was empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Start ed For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANTHRACITE bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid while saving ground approaching the quarter pole, kicked clear in the stretch and held that margin to the wire while drifting mildly. MINTENON raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and gained ground late. TUNA N STAMPS chased the leader from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the three path and kept on to the finish. KENRIC led the way from the two path around the first turn, opened up on the field racing up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path around the far turn and weakened in the lane. MAGNA RULER bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, raced in the four path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, angled in to save ground around the second bend and finished evenly while never threatening. FUN AT THE FORT saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch and around the far turn and made no bid. ISLANDMAN bumped with the horse to his outside and steadied at the start, raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and was empty. ERLAN raced in the three path around the first turn, trailed well behind the field in the middle of the track up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and never factored.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 19. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR FANTASY tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the turn and drew off in the lane. LYRICAL chased the pace setter on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the four and five path and kept on to the finish. LADY TEUFLESBERG brushed with the horse to her inside at the start, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn, was caught entering the stretch and weakened in the final furlong. CALENDULA raced in the middle of the pack early, came around the bend in the two path and flattened out in the stretch. BOURBON BLAST bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, settled off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three and four path and made no bid. AUBURN brushed with the horse to his outside at the break, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considere d In Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHICAGO RIVER bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path racing around the turn and drew off in the lane. MORE MUCHO chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend and kept on in the stretch. MY GIRL MELLY raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the early going, challenged from the three and four path coming around the turn and chased the top two home from there. HOLLYWOOD HONEY dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and weakened in the stretch. LADYNESS trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane while never threatening. BELLA ROMANCE dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, dropped back while racing in the two path around the bend and tired further in the lane. ANNA'S IMAGE bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, raced off the pace early, came around the turn in the two path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 68. Claiming Purse 22500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Two Such Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLEASANT VALIANT bobbled leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first turn, pressed the pace between horses up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the three path and kicked clear in the lane. GODS GLORY led the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far turn and chased the winner home late, just holding second. CESAR raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and gained ground late, narrowly missing the place. SLIPPERY WHEN WET saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and finished evenly. HOP AND SCOTCH hopped up leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and passed tiring horses in the stretch. FLYING SUN raced in the two path early, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path and flattened out in the lane. ASPLUNDER saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the four path and faded in the stretch. DENYING trailed the field on the rail through the opening half mile, saved ground around the second turn and made no bid. ROCK CHALK raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the second bend from the two path and was empty in the lane.

JOYOUS FAIRY TALE raced in the two path early, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the far bend and faded in the stretch. BLACK KARMA raced off the pace in the four path around the first turn, trailed the field coming up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the four path and showed no threat. REBATE bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, saved ground around the first bend, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and made no bid. DRILL'S VALENTINE chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.
